  "original_title": "\u0d89\u0db1\u0dca\u0db0\u0db1 \u0d9c\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1 \u2018\u0da7\u0ddd\u0d9a\u0db1\u0dca\u2019 \u0d9a\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0db8\u0dba \u0d89\u0dc0\u0dbb\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The 'token' system to buy fuel is over",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Electricity and Energy Minister Mr. Kanchana Wijesekera said today (3) afternoon that the 'token' system will not be implemented at Cipetco petrol stations and the 'token' system is not implemented by the government but by security agencies.",
        "When there was no fuel, the people who were hopelessly waiting in the queues at the end of last month were given 'tokens' to remove them from the queues and after getting the fuel again, those people will get priority. The Minister said that he is in talks with the Chief of Defense Staff General Shavendra Silva to end the 'token' system. and did.",
        "The minister said that a system will be prepared to provide fuel and also asked the people not to go to queues to get 'tokens'."
      ],
